'cause I know it deals with life

00:00:57.057 --> 00:00:58.626 align:middle line:90%
after death and many others.

00:00:58.626 --> 00:01:00.494 align:middle line:84%
>> Anthony Peake: The first book
is "Is There Life After Death?"

00:01:00.494 --> 00:01:02.630 align:middle line:84%
the extraordinary signs of
what happens when you die

00:01:02.630 --> 00:01:04.832 align:middle line:90%
which was published in 2006.

00:01:04.832 --> 00:01:07.968 align:middle line:84%
That book has now sold
probably approaching 40,000

00:01:07.968 --> 00:01:09.170 align:middle line:90%
copies worldwide.

00:01:09.170 --> 00:01:13.107 align:middle line:84%
It's been translated into
Russian, Dutch, Spanish,

00:01:13.107 --> 00:01:14.742 align:middle line:90%
various other languages as well.

00:01:14.742 --> 00:01:17.478 align:middle line:84%
On top of that, the second book
was then called "The Daemon,

00:01:17.478 --> 00:01:19.680 align:middle line:84%
A Guide to Your Extraordinary
Secret Self"

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:21.682 align:middle line:84%
which discusses the
idea of human duality,

00:01:21.682 --> 00:01:23.551 align:middle line:90%
the idea of do we have two foci

00:01:23.551 --> 00:01:25.819 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness
within the brain.

00:01:25.819 --> 00:01:29.022 align:middle line:84%
The third book is then "The
Out-of-Body Experience"

00:01:29.022 --> 00:01:32.560 align:middle line:84%
which is my scientific take
on exactly what happens

00:01:32.560 --> 00:01:36.197 align:middle line:84%
when people feel that they
move outside of their body.

00:01:36.197 --> 00:01:39.366 align:middle line:84%
I've then written a book on time
called "The Labyrinth of Time"

00:01:39.366 --> 00:01:42.570 align:middle line:84%
which is the science of
the consciousness of time,

00:01:42.570 --> 00:01:46.040 align:middle line:84%
how we perceive time, does
time flow, can time speed up

00:01:46.040 --> 00:01:48.375 align:middle line:90%
or slow down, is time circular.

00:01:48.375 --> 00:01:53.247 align:middle line:84%
I've then written a book,
I co-written a book,

00:01:53.247 --> 00:01:56.450 align:middle line:84%
so I say co-written but
actually co-edited a book

00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:59.787 align:middle line:84%
with two Australian
consultant psychiatrists

00:01:59.787 --> 00:02:01.822 align:middle line:84%
on the near death experience
called "Making Sense

00:02:01.822 --> 00:02:05.559 align:middle line:84%
of Near-Death Experience" which
funny enough was nominated

00:02:05.559 --> 00:02:07.194 align:middle line:84%
for the Psychiatric
Book of the Year

00:02:07.194 --> 00:02:09.396 align:middle line:84%
of the British Medical
Association last year,

00:02:09.396 --> 00:02:11.699 align:middle line:84%
and we still ended up
being highly commended.

00:02:11.699 --> 00:02:14.335 align:middle line:84%
So clearly this work has
very much been registered

00:02:14.335 --> 00:02:18.906 align:middle line:84%
by serious workers and
serious scientists.

00:02:18.906 --> 00:02:21.675 align:middle line:84%
I then wrote and at the
moment I'm in the process

00:02:21.675 --> 00:02:25.746 align:middle line:84%
of writing two books and I've
just finished a book called

00:02:25.746 --> 00:02:30.084 align:middle line:84%
"The Infinite Mindfield" which
is dealing with consciousness

00:02:30.084 --> 00:02:32.786 align:middle line:84%
in the way consciousness
can sometimes

00:02:32.786 --> 00:02:35.723 align:middle line:84%
under certain circumstances
perceive alternative realities.

00:02:35.723 --> 00:02:38.324 align:middle line:84%
And I'm particularly
interested in the idea

00:02:38.324 --> 00:02:40.861 align:middle line:84%
of when we dream,
where do we go.

00:02:40.861 --> 00:02:42.496 align:middle line:84%
What exactly is the
reality there?

00:02:42.496 --> 00:02:45.733 align:middle line:84%
What happens when people take
hallucinogenic substances

00:02:45.733 --> 00:02:48.302 align:middle line:84%
like dimethyltryptamine
and such like?

00:02:48.302 --> 00:02:50.304 align:middle line:90%
And I'm working closely there

00:02:50.304 --> 00:02:52.406 align:middle line:84%
with a guy called
Professor Ervin Laszlo

00:02:52.406 --> 00:02:54.408 align:middle line:90%
who is a Hungarian--

00:02:54.408 --> 00:02:55.442 align:middle line:90%
[ Inaudible Remark ]

